<!--Headings-->
<h1>Discover the flavors of Thailand</h1>
Tom Yum Goong: A spicy Thai Delight
Ingredients
<br>
<!--Paragraph-->
<p>Tom Yum Goong is a classic Thai soup renowned for its bold flavors and aromatic spices. This hot and sour soup features a tantalizing blend of lemongrass, galangal, and kaffir lime leaves, combined with succulent shrimp.</p>
<!--Blockquote-->
<blockquote>"The key to a delicious Tom Yum Goong lies in the balance of flavors - sweet, sour, salty, and spicy." - Chef Somchai
</blockquote>
<!--Ingredients-->
<ul>
<li><strong>Lemongrass</strong>: 2stalks</li>
<li><strong>Thai basil</strong>:1 cup</li>
<li><strong>Kaffir Lime Leaves</strong>: 3 leaves</li>
<li><strong>Shrimp</strong>: 500</li>
</ul>
<!--Preparation Steps-->
<h3>Preparation</h3>
<ol>
<li><em>Simmer</em> both for 10 minutes.</li>
<li>Add lemongrass, galangal and kaffir lime leaves.</li>
<li>Stir in shrimp and cook until pink.</li>
<li>Season with fish sauce, lime juice, and chili paste.</li>
<li>Garnish with Thai basil and serve hot.</li>
</ol>
<!--Cooking Tips-->
<h3>Cooking tips</h3>
<ul>
<li>1/2 cup of fish sauce adds authentic Thai food</li>
<li>1 tbsp of chili paste gives the soup its signature heat</li>
</li>
</ul>
